Issues =================
- Is caGrid access in scope for 1.0?
- Assumption is that some data sets are specific to a given analysis tool, but some data sets may be applicable to multiple tools. Is this correct?
- Need to discuss DataSet components that are statically defined (lists) vs. dynamic (queried).
- Need to further refine DataSet, DataGround and AnalysisMethod relationships.
- How will Research Investigators be associated to studies? Who manages access?
- How do we represent summary data (e.g. percent of clinical attributes correlated to up regulated gene)
The TrWorkbench Administrator is responsible for account and shared annotation management for a given TrWorkbench installation.
A Study Manager is responsible for the definition and configuration of one or more studies.
Data Service represents the various external systems that TrWorkbench uses as data sources (NCIA, caArray, etc.) for studies.
An Analysis Tool is an external analysis or visualization tool that TrWorkbench is configured to integrate with and launch for study data.
An authorized user of the TrWorkbench system.
A Research Investigator uses TrWorkbench to review data and perform analyses on translational data to answer scientific questions.
Externa Client System represents any external system (caBIG or otherwise) that retrieves data via the exposed caBIG Silver or caGrid APIs.
In this use case, an External System retrieves study data or user data sets via the exposed caBIG Silver or caGrid APIs.
In this use case, a potential TrWorkbench User requests an account for access.
In this use case, a Research Investigator views and updates the content of his workspace which consists of subscribed studies, data sets and analysis results.
A TrWorkbench User authenticates his credentials in order to use the system.
In this use case, a Radiologist views or downloads images associated with a study.

In this use case, a Study Manager defines the structure of a study which may consist of clinical data, imaging data and genomic data and deploys it for use. The items that are defined are the structure and source of data and the analysis tools to be associated with the study.
In this use case, the Study Manager permits access to restricted studies or study data to specific Research Investigators.
In this use case, the TrWorkbench Administrator loads or updates annotation for entities that are shared between studies including genomic and array reporter annotation.
In this use case, a Study Author revises the structure and of the study and the data content based on changes to the data in the originating Data Service.
In this use case, a Research Investigator creates or edits a list of data intended for export or to be analyzed using an integrated analysis tool.
In this use case, a Research Investigator defines, updates or executes a query (which may be saved) that can be used to locate a set of study data that meets specific criteria.
In this use case, a Research Investigator applies an analysis or visualization method to a new or previously defined data set.
In this use case, a Research Investigator reviews the available data in a study via search and browse tools.
